{{ja-kanjitab|ばち|yomi=k|alt=撥,枹:uncommon}}

From the ''kan'yōyomi'' of the {{m|ja|撥}} kanji spelling, in turn a shift in pronunciation from the regular ''kan'on'' reading of ''hatsu''.<ref name="K">{{R:Kojien}}</ref>

First cited to the ''{{w|Wamyō Ruijushō}}'' from 934 {{CE}}.<ref name="KDJ2">{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten 2|撥・桴・枹}}</ref>

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|ばち|acc=2|acc_ref=DJR,SMK5,NHK}}<!-- If you look this up in the NHK, look up by kana spelling ばち: the online version at Sakura Paris has a typo, misspelling this as 揆 in kanji, which has no ''bachi'' reading. -->

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|ばち|バチ}}

# {{defdate|from 934}} {{ja-def|桴|枹}} a [[drum stick]] for instruments such as the [[taiko]] and [[gong]], a [[percussion]] [[mallet]]
#: {{synonyms|ja|桴#Japanese:_buchi|alt1=桴|tr1=buchi|q1=see below}}
# {{defdate|from 1001}} {{ja-def|撥}} the [[plectra]] or [[pick]]s used to play the [[biwa]] [[lute]] and [[shamisen]]
# {{defdate|from 1233}} {{ja-def|撥|桴}} in {{m|ja|雅楽||tr=gagaku|traditional Japanese court music}}, the [[plectra]] or [[pick]]s used to play the [[biwa]] [[lute]] and [[shamisen]], together with the [[stick]]s and other objects held by the [[dancer]] in {{m|ja|舞楽||tr=bugaku|traditional Japanese court dance}}
# {{defdate|from 1766}} {{lb|ja|traditional Japanese|_|shipbuilding}} a [[metal]] [[chisel]] [[mallet]] {{q|from the general resemblance in shape to a gong mallet}}

