===Etymology 2===
{{etymid|ja|buchi}}
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|ぶち}}

Shift from ''bachi'' above, possibly influenced by or otherwise related to nominal form ''buchi'' of verb {{m|ja|打つ|tr=butsu||to strike, to hit}}, itself a shift from ''utsu''.

First attested in 1650.<ref name="KDJ2-buchi">{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten 2}}</ref>  This pronunciation of the term appears to be falling out of use, and is not included in modern pitch-accent dictionaries.<ref name="KDJ2O-buti">{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten 2 Online|ぶち 【桴】|lid=200203af41c6n64Rplnb|kotobank=ぶち 【桴】}}</ref><ref name="DJR"/><ref name="NHK"/><ref name="SMK5"/>

